    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>Supradictus autem <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1989">Teuto</persName>, causa
                        utilitatis huius <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs> [<orgName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1900">Sancti Vincencii in
                            Vulturno</orgName>], <rs key="#Commutatio">commutavit</rs> cum <rs
                            key="#Princeps">principibus</rs> Beneventanis res et possessiones, quas
                        habebat in Caudetanis [<rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> inclitam in <rs
                            key="#City_territory">finibus</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Curtes #Slave #Slave labour #City_territory"
                            ref="#places/2800">Caudetanis</placeName>, loco qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Inflow #Purchase #Slave"
                            ref="#places/2399"><geogName
                                key="#Commutatio #Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Inflow #Purchase #Slave"
                                ref="#estates/1925">Paulisi</geogName></placeName>, cum <rs
                            key="#Slave #Slave_labour">servis</rs> et ancillis], a quibus accepit
                        possessiones et res inclitas, cum <rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Commutatio #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1904">Sancte Dei genitricis Marie</orgName>, que
                        vocatur in <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#places/2330">Oliveto</placeName>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>CV I, tra nn. 65-66, p. 315; CV III, doc. perduti, n. 36/4, pp. 141-142</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The curtis mentioned as the object of the exchange in the <foreign>Chronicon
                        Vulturnensis</foreign> was left to the monastery of San Vincenzo al Volturno
                    fifty years earlier by Radeprandus, son of Radeprandus, in his will (CV I, no.
                    34, pp. 249-251).</p>
            </div>
